name: Becky Strahle
bio: Author of Seeing God in the Sweet Ordinary. Here, you'll find colorful daily art, travel, family, beauty... a focus on His goodness. Welcome🤗

social_posts.post_text: Good morning friends! I just restocked the notecard packs. Each design comes with five cards and envelopes. Backs are blank so you can fill in your own message. Wouldn't it be a sweet goal to write more notes to the people we love?🥰🥰🥰 Happy Hump day!
Our "Pursuit of Peace" calendar is $5.00 off this week only:)) Don't wait! The shop is closing for the holidays soon🥰

I just found a new account yesterday @dmirgonfit21. She's 51 and looks incredible.  I turn 50 in May and I have a health goal to lose 25 pounds. But honestly if I just made self care a daily habit that would be the sweetest reward. It's been a mind trap for me for far too long. I'll post what workouts I do with her. Anyone want to do it with me?

A feeling of home is what we're all looking for. The truth is this world will never meet that need, but when we know Jesus we have the confidence to approach the throne. He paid it all. He knows our pain and suffering. Our rejection and dismay. Becoming flesh and blood He experienced it all and with that there's sympathy and compassion. There's no shame. Because of grace we can be in His presence and experience all the good things to come. Hebrews 4 is so good. 

Loving this tree tunnel from Maui. The way the trees envelope you is like a warm hug. I'm practicing art this next year by delving into scripture.  There's no better way for it to come alive for me🎨 #farmgirlpaintsscripture Feel free to join along and tag me.

This photo holds a plethora of memories.  Maggie had just graduated from high school. We were on a grand adventure in FRANCE! My girl @audaciousdaughter lives every moment to the fullest, so we thought we'd go on a bike ride. Next thing you know she's thrown from her bike and she's in the ditch... full of thorny weeds. She laughs things off, but I know it hurt. 

How often do we brush off hurts? As I was reading through scripture today and struggling with my own emotional roller coaster of thoughts, the Lord whispered to me I'm His. My identity... My very being isn't dependent on my circumstances, my feelings, my past etc... Jesus dwells in me and has invaded my spaces.  Praise God🙌 Because of Him I'm a new creation. My thoughts. My actions. My every move is changed because He lives in me. If you're feeling in the weeds... and you just want to lay there and disappear remember Whose you are. If you know Him...you are a child of the One True King! Rise up daughter and get back on the seat...

Inspired by this beautiful garden I visited a few years ago @wendylouiseleonard!! The Word for today is from Romans 8. If you haven't read it in a while it's a golden nugget of truth. Are you a dead man walking?? Living according to the flesh instead of the Spirit? When we live and walk in the Spirit we have Life and Peace🙌🙌🙌 Join me #dailypainter #nashvilleartist #waxpastels @carandache
Light snuck through today and the impact was undeniable. It felt like technicolor. Also, this song...what in the world is he saying?😂😂😂

My word for next year is play. And I'll be honest, being the little striver bee that I am I find play challenging😂 But I'm excited to see what will come from cutting up cardboard and playing with crayons. Because if God whispers it to me He's got something in mind👊🏼🙌 

I fell in love with Sheryl Cochran's work when we were in Maine earlier this year and I've had this gravitational pull toward making my own cardboard birds. This is my first attempt. I shall call him Ollie the owl;) Go check out her work @cardboardsea.

My devotional this morning (New Morning Mercies by Tripp) was on the sin of self reliance. One sentence stood out..."you'll never make it on your own." Ouch! I'm like Lord, What image goes with THAT for my journal practice?? And immediately I turned to this page in my Chatbook!! My precious niece @itsbrittanystuart on her wedding day😭🙌 

On our wedding day we are released into the care of our groom. Ties are cut and new covenant bonds are formed. Just like when we give our hearts to the Lord He steps in as our groom...provider...lover of our heart and soul... Saving us from a lifetime of separation.  We're united forever!! When we take on self reliance it's the opposite of our "marriage vows." For some reason this just hit me square. Lift the veil, look your groom in the eye and give over self...

A little Maine lighthouse.  Light just makes all the difference. I'm bathed in it out here in the greenhouse today🙌

Reading in Philippians 2:9... every knee will bow, in heaven and on earth and under the earth, and every tongue will confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of the Father. In this dark world we must shine bright. The day is coming friends...

I finally got around to drying oranges slices yesterday. I've been seeing that simple Scandinavian decoration for years and had yet to try it. 

It took forever! Like 9 hours or so, but so worth it!! I'm a light lover, so seeing this pop of color just warms my heart. I might leave it up all year long😁

Question for you... I have a ton left over. Should I add more pieces hanging low and fill up the window?

Recipe:
Slice orange slices 4-5 mm thick
Place on cookie sheet or drying rack.
170 degrees for 6-9 hours. Flip a few times. Check occasionally:)
Poke string through with a toothpick.

I had a few left over orange slices from this morning, so a little mobile in the greenhouse seemed fitting. By itself it looked a little barren, nothing a bright cardboard cardinal couldnt remedy. I'm naming him Twitch after that dancer that passed away recently. His beautiful smile was contagious.

Good Monday morning friends. There's something about putting on fun pair earrings that make you feel ready for the day;)) Loving these wintery owls by my girlie @audaciousdaughter. She's sold out, but there are a few other styles still left in her shop🥰

I had the most vivid euphoric dream the other night. Brian and I were in a convertible driving in a field of brightly colored irises. They were so tall they were touching our hands and pushing against the car. 

The field was blinding with color. I remember feeling so happy and carefree. Laughing! When I woke up I immediately looked up what irises meant and among other good things...what caught my eye was that it's the Tennessee state flower!  And it means the year of spiritual insight🥰😱🥳 Yes, Lord I want all of that. Surrounding beauty. Fields of hope and color. Friendship. Purity. A year of spiritual insight. This is my prayer. Let it be so! Bring on 2023! I can't wait to see what awaits!!

#journaling #colormehappy #irises #paintyourdreans #farmgirlpaintsscripture

I've been receiving some of the best feedback from the book. Messages from women saying this message is ministering to me in the season I'm in! Ya'll I can't even begin to tell you how that touches my heart. As I was praying over this book that is EXACTLY what I prayed! God is so faithful. 

It's been a long time since I wrote the book, so this morning I reread through it again. And you know what? It even ministered to me😂😂 This page and Psalm 51 touched my heart!! I'd love to hear your experience.  Did God use this book to touch your heart? Please let me know or leave an Amazon review! I read them. It encourages me in this new season of figuring out what's next!! #seeinggodinthesweetordinary #linkinprofile

My precious Momma Dixie turns 80 today🥳🥳 To say she's been a vital part of my life is an understatement. She's been my spiritual mentor, my prayer warrior, my cheerleader and champion. She's been my friend. The one who leans in, never leaves, and is always for me. We love her with all our hearts. So grateful God gave me this woman to be my momma. Happy birthday foxy lady!! You shine!!!#blessedbeyondmeasure #mommadixie #happybirthday

We hit Versailles today. It's always been on my bucket list. To say that it was over the top opulence is an understatement. So hard to believe people actually lived there...4,000 at one point. The King loved his adoration. 

We got the audio tour, which we highly recommend. I wish the weather would have held off. I know the gardens would have been fun to explore and Marie Antoinette's farmette. That would have been my favorite. 

Sure love my people!! Making lots of memories on this sweet trip.  See my stories if you've missed our first few days of Paris🥰 I made a highlight...Paris 2.0.

How do I begin to sum up 2022? It was full to brim with milestones, huge steps of faith, celebrations galore. The girls both graduated, Brian and I celebrated 30 years, the book released, we gathered LOTS of precious people to our hill, my momma turned eighty...we traveled far and wide🙌 

Instead of holding back, it was a year of bravely pushing forward. I'm forever in awe at how the Lord has graciously held us close and propelled us all to our limits. The stretch has been uncomfortable and liberating at the same time. If there's something you want to do...do it! Don't overthink a thing. I'm actually going to miss you 2022! It's been a while since I felt that way about a year;) Here's to 2023... I have a feeling the upcoming unknowns are going to be spectacular ✨️🥳

We made it home late last night. Exhausted, grateful, counting our miracles🙌

It's amazing how travel fulfills it's purpose. The change of scenery, pace, creature comforts does an internal realigning. Having a bathroom nearby equates luxury😂 Those blinders come off. You notice the things you take for granted. 

You also notice the things you want to change. For me it's the little things.. walking more, eating as healthy as possible and homemaking. I want to cook and eat at home more. Preparing a table for sharing our day.

I loved the people we met along our journey. I need more of that too. Connection. My favorite thing about our little neighborhood in Paris is that I was constantly envisioning their daily routine.  A fresh baguette run in the morning. A pitstop at their flower market and grocery for that night's dinner. Familiar faces. All within walking distance. Gah! 

It's so different and yet it doesn't have to be. Routines and habits can be changed. Tweaks can be made it's just a matter of paying attention and stepping out.  I may not live in France, but I can incorporate some of their lifestyle:)) 

I'm ready for some new. How about you? **Oh and our hotel didn't have televisions. A week without the noise was something I'm definitely keen on keeping. Love you peeps!

I got up the nerve to ask my publisher @harvesthousepublishers how the book was doing. Why does that take a peptalk😂🙈🥴

I'm sharing with you because I know ya'll are in my corner and we want the same thing. To point people to Jesus. To encourage others in their faithwalk. To help lift people out of the dark places with His truth! 

My numbers are not dismal for a new author, but it could be doing a LOT better. She said one thing that would really help is if I had more reviews. 

I know ya'll are loving it. I've had the sweetest feedback. Will you do me a really BIG favor and go to Amazon and write the same thing? I know it takes time, but it would help so much.  Share how the book has encouraged you. Share how you've sent the prayers to a friend going through hard places. Share how you love the art. Share whatever God puts on your heart, but please share! It matters a LOT. I want this book to go far and wide and get in the hands of those who need it. 

A lot of you know I'm also praying for Cracker Barrel to pick it up. My contact approached them and they turned it down at this time, but she's going to try again in the spring. Keep praying! God is BIG. He hears our prayers. He can make a way🙌🙌🙌 Love you peeps!! I can't thank you enough for coming along side me in the new thing.

We've had two very near car crashes this week. Terrifyingly close. 

One was on the way to pick up our Favor from the kennel. We were behind a car that made a sudden turn and the car behind us didn't see the signal. They slammed on their brakes almost rear-ending us. There was another car driving past us at the same time. It would have been bad.

Then this morning on the way to church an oncoming car came into our lane and almost hit the truck in front of us head on... causing him to swerve off the road. We were on a road with construction and he ran over barrels to get off the road. Crazy😳🙊

It feels like our angels are working overtime. I can almost see it in the supernatural...this dome of protection. Have ya'll been experiencing anything like this? So grateful for how God hems us in before and behind. I make it a practice to pray and release our angels for protection. Just thought I'd share...

I started out this morning super heavy. I could feel depressing thoughts racing through my head on repeat. I'm not going to lie winter is a struggle for me. I'm solar powered and the sun really affects my moods. 

I decided to take a walk and combat the lies with God's truth. His word. When the barrage comes that's what I do. I have to take my thoughts captive or it's just a free fall. 

Not long after, I had the sweetest phone call that reminded me of something to be excited about. And then a new friend messaged me that my book that I gave her was really touching her heart. I swear the Lord put both of those women in my path today as a love hug. If someone comes to mind don't hesitate reaching out. You have no idea what they're struggling with. Your call may just be the buoy that keeps them a float:)) 

Loved this pic in my feed of summer.That blue sky and my zinnias🥰 It'll be here before we know it.

Trying oil pastels today. I bought the creamiest set of @sennelier1887 pastels in Paris and today was my first day EVER using them. I'm completely smitten. I think the hardest part of being a creative is figuring out what to create. Having reference photos saves me. I use my Chatbooks alot! This is my Illinois country road I grew up on. Every summer periwinkle blueblooms of chicory fill the ditches. Not a bad first attempt:))

We're in Colorado visiting my niece @itsbrittanystuart and her hubby @itsjustinstuart. This our very first silk scarf project! I'm so proud at how they turned out. Learning is GOOD for the soul y'all. I'll be teaching this extremely satisfying art process in Bellagio, ITALY in June @artandfaithcreative. By then @audaciousdaughter, @felicity.strahle and I are going to be pros😁😁😁

I think sometimes the Lord brings us to a standstill so we can see our world frozen in time. I've been going at a very fast pace for many years. And to be honest the still has always frightened me a bit. I need a plan. I need forward motion. But what if I really need to quit straining towards something and just look at what's already there. Just some thoughts on this frozen morning. Does the in-between freak you out too? Because that's what a slow down feels like for me.  A void. When in actuality it could just be the filling I need... #frozen

I'm loving my new media fast schedule. On Friday nights I uninstall Instagram. Amazing how it takes a beat to get used to not checking my phone constantly. The freedom of being present is a gift. I read a fast challenge of one day a week, one week a month and one month a year. I decided to do every weekend. And the week and month too. My "rhythm" may be messed up, but my heart is more at peace and that's what I'm longing for:)) Curious how do y'all stay balanced??

My @audaciousdaughter girl turned 23 today. She's absolutely spectacular!! You know what I'm loving the most as my girls grow up? That they are my friends😭🙌 Relationships morph in these early adulthood years. There are occasional challenges at times...yes, but the sweet spot of developed respect and mutual friendship is honestly what I've been waiting for since the very beginning. I love this time. Holding on with both hands!!

Good morning friends.  Happy Valentine's day. In case you forgot, the God of the Universe knows your name. He knows the number of hairs on your head. In an act of extravagant love He knit you together in your mother's womb. You are special, one of a kind and there's a beautiful plan for your life. You are SO loved that God sent His son Jesus to die just for you...so you could walk free, whole, forgiven. Now let's walk worthy of that gift and show everyone around us who Jesus is.  #lovedtobelove

Did you know it's okay not to trust yourself? It's biblical actually. Our feelings are fickle. Case in point I'm perimenopausal. I've been seeing a change in my hormones for years... weight gain, low energy, joint pain, brain fog, anxiety, depression, 7 years of tinnitus...all the things. But this year the loss of motivation came. The lack of interest in things that used to get me out of bed in the morning. And honestly it feels like too much at times. In addition to the body changes, you add this little nugget and having to push to do everything and it's really sad. It's not who I am. 

But it's not every day. One day I'm fine and the next day I'm not. If I made decisions based on how I "feel." My emotions... It would be a train wreck. I think God wrote Proverbs 28:26 just for me...Those who trust in themselves are fools, but those who walk in wisdom are kept safe.

No matter what season of life we're walking through our entire focus has to gaze upon Him. His truth. His promises. His goodness. The enemy of our souls is out to steal, kill and destroy. My job is turn my eyes upon Jesus, period. Seasons change. Trials come and go. He always remains the same. 

For those of you who'll want to help I'm all ears. I've been on HRT (second attempt) for a few weeks. This is after years of birth control I took to help with terrible cramps. I take homeopathic remedies and supplements. I'm trying to eat better, get exercise in. Sauna. Anything that helps. 

Pic by @tisha_lyn 
#menopause #trust #change

The sun popped out this afternoon bringing with it all the feels. Give me all the dancing shadows, sunbeams and slivers of hope for a soon approaching spring! I saw redbuds, daffodils and forsythia in bloom today. If that doesn't lift the mood I don't know what does. Thank you Lord for Your glimpses of beauty! I will fulfill my duty of basking in it's glow:))
A little Saturday morning art session. Gouache on clayboard. It dried almost as soon as I applied.  Super thin layers...so, many many layers.

Hi friends! Pressing pause on here for four weeks. I've always wanted to be intentional with my time and I've found that my self control is horrible with this app. So the timing is perfect for a time out. I'm going to be preparing for the @tararoyersteele event, working on a big art project and hopefully getting into a rhythm with self care. I'd love your prayers. Email me if you need to get in touch. Love ya'll 💓💓💓

A month ago I uninstalled all of my distractions, sat my phone down, and with giant exhale I felt my shoulders relax. The next morning on my walk, as I was praying, I felt the Lord whisper "Finally, I have your attention😭😭!" And then the next steps and download came🙌🙌🙌

Needless, to say I was way overdue on being obedient in this area. And to be honest, I'm not really ready to be here yet. Here's what I do know... after this week I'm uninstalling it again and changing my methods😃 I bought a laptop and I'm using it to do Instagram and BLOGGING AGAIN!! I've pulled out my big girl camera. I'm going back to my roots. Remembering why I started this public journey. And I couldn't be more excited. I hope you'll go there with me as I figure stuff out. I wrote my first post "The Great Reset"...the link is in my profile under blog;)

As for today!! My @audaciousdaughter and I are headed to Mississippi to pick us up one @honeyholden. Then were off to speak at @tararoyersteele event in Round Top, Texas with another dear friend @tara_dickson. 

I've had a whole month to sit in what the Lord is preparing me to say. It's been a lifetime of lessons in relationships with women... Friendship hurts, rejection and healing. I can't wait to take my story and give Him glory!!! There are still tickets available.  Feel the nudge to join us? Please come!!!! It's going to be EPIC😂🥳🥳🥳🥳 Missed you precious peeps🥰🥰

Our road trip to speak at @tararoyersteele gathering isn't even over yet and so many memories have been made. I feel the Lord lavishly loving on us. There's something about obedience and stepping out into the uncomfortable that brings you such dependence. And we all know how much the Lord loves dependence. 

As I've been preparing to speak (my first time), and nerves start to rise up...He's been reminding me over and over again "it's not about me." 

Since I'm reading through the Old Testament right now I keep thinking about Moses and how he didn't want to speak. He had a speech impediment and God gave him Aaron to help him. He still spoke to Moses though...he wasn't off the hook😂 He was called to do this big thing and He did it even though he didn't feel able. 

Go tell your story. The triumphs, the hurt, the healing, the God stories. It's our legacy as believers... It buoys others faith and gives them hope to cling to. So I'll get up there tonight, and despite my butterflies He'll fill my mouth with His words and His name will be glorified🙌 Whoosh!!! What an honor🤗

Sorry I've been slow to share friends. Last week was a whirlwind, and then we came home and the grief in our community over the Nashville shootings was palpable. It just didn't feel right to share our @tararoyersteele gathering yet. 

How do you begin to sum up SO much? First of all my heart is so full. I was nervous about speaking and of course the second I opened my mouth the Holy Spirit filled it and I didn't even look at my notes🙌 It just flowed. Thank you for praying!! Our messages, @honeyholden and @tara_dickson, just intertwined beautifully and you could just sense His hand orchestrating the whole night. 

I'm absolutely smitten with all the new people I met this week and the work @tararoyersteele is doing in her community.  She has so many giftings, but the one that humbled and inspired me to the core was her heart for gathering. She has this huge welcome sign that seems to hang above her head, and it's flashing bright for all to see. God is doing amazing things down there in Texas and it was such an honor to have just a tiny toe involved in it.

I feel like the word for me was step out and watch Him do it. He bridges our insecurities with His faithfulness. He communicates for us when we feel inadequate and He uses us if we are willing. It's evident in the lives that have been changed through this ministry. If you'd like to be a part in @tararoyersteele vision dm her. She'll find something for you to do😂 SO much more to share!! Stay tuned.

Somehow God was gracious enough to let us wiggle our way into the precious @honeyholden and @nickholden family several years ago. We've met every member now (except Lauren). We've sat at their tables and bowed our hearts in prayer. 

We've been lavishly loved on... Served, time and again. We've heard their countless family stories. Experienced their grandkids personalities. Walked their church sanctuary. Shopped in their neck of the woods😉 Heard @nickholden mini sermons. It's been the best kind of friendship immersion and honestly I've been going through withdrawal the last few days😂

I'm in absolute awe at how tightly knit they all are. They FaceTime with the girls and their families every.single.day. Nothing is too miniscule to stop and pray over. It's been a joy to watch, and an honor to be witness to. It's left me inspired to the core. This is how it should be😄 

Oh that we would wholly love God and serve others like Jesus did. That's the goal... The whole reason we exist. Til next time sweet Holden family. We love ya'll and thank you from the bottom of our hearts for loving us back❤❤

Hi friends. I hope you all had a beautiful Easter. I didn't take one picture of my family😮 It felt like a giant mom fail looking back, but we were just in the moment and it didn't happen. But I did have my honey take a picture of me later in the day, when I stood in the middle of our bathroom weeping at the pure joy and beauty of a disco ball!🤣 You should have seen his face. Confused doesn't really describe it. I blogged about the ball and a few other things if you want to read more...link is in profile

The whole shop just went on sale for Mother's day!! 15% off through May 1st. Book, anointing oil and hankies, candles, pillows, cuffs, sweatshirt, necklaces, a few handpainted bags, love letters, ornaments...the framed prints🥳🙌🙌 No code needed!! Go bless yo momma and yourself:))

Did you know we took my artwork and made a luxury pillow line? These are handmade from the finest fabrics, down filled...sweet ball trim. They just make the space infused with color and creativity.  I have a few left. Don't miss the momma sale. No code needed:)) Link in profile. @reba_ye

I've had Psalms 23 on my heart all year long. It plays like a record over and over again in my mind. The beginning..."I shall not want." Means to me, He supplies all my needs. When I look to Him the discontent melts away. But that's only if I look to Him. 

I painted this painting awhile back and it has the last part of Psalms 23 on it. If you are ever in question of how much the Lord loves you read this. 

This little print is tucked in with the hankies and anointing oils in my shop. It's a sweet reminder of how good our God is.

My girls went to a secular concert last night. During the show the singer proclaimed her beliefs. Shouting proudly about abortion, lesbian day and her lack of faith in God etc... The crowd erupted in applause. Cheering...hands raised. This is our world friends. We know it. We see it. We feel the heaviness of it. It's lost. But we know the answer. We have His truth tucked in our hearts. Jesus is the ONLY way! He's the truth. Our path to everlasting life! 

My response was anger. The singer was operating in an anti-christ spirit. Spewing lies to an adoring audience of followers. Influencing, those searching, to ultimate destruction. 

My youngest response was sadness. Her eyes filled with tears and she ran to the bathroom to compose herself. The holy spirit inside of her grieving for those who don't know Him. 

Our pastor the other day reminded us that this life is our one chance to share about the Lord. In Heaven we'll all know Him. There will be no sin. Our good news assignment will be over and a new one will be in play. If we don't share as boldly as the world does who will? The enemy's voice is loud. Ours doesn't have to match. A whisper of TRUTH is like a megaphone in a dark dark world. Our sliver of His light in us will pierce the blackness. 

Ask Him how to share. Ask Him how to love. For such a time is this friends. We have the privilege of living in the last days. Isn't that amazing!! We will all stand before Him SOON and Every. Single. Knee shall bow, and every single tongue shall confess that Jesus Christ is Lord🙌🙌🙌

Happy 50th birthday to our @levrage7. We celebrate who you are! Steady, faithfilled, passionate, hard working, kind and so very generous with your time and care of us. So many good things in our lives are because of you. We see you and honor the gift God gave us when He created YOU!! Love you baby!! Here's to five decades!! Bring it:)))

Because my feed needs some color:)) 

I think people associate the desert with the color brown. But I see the neutrals as a backdrop for the brightest pops of color you can fathom. It's a show stopper. Most of the plants and flowers that thrive in the sun are usually colorful. I think there's a lesson there... #colormehappy #palmsprings I've made a highlight if you've missed my stories. The beauty here is simply overwhelming.

I decided to do an upclose tour of our airbnb. The decor was very neutral. Light woods. Macrame hangings. Whites and creams. The only pops of color were pastel pillows and plants. Which I truly found so soothing, but all of the TEXTURE surrounding us was the true star. The landscape was layered with beauty and interest. Amazing what you see when you lean in close.

We had our finger on the cancel button. We booked (impulsively) to celebrate our 50th birthdays and then immediately we felt like maybe we shouldn't. The Italy retreat is coming up... Would we miss the girls too much? But we had the miles and in our hearts we knew alone time would be good for us. I'm so glad we slept on it, changed our minds, and didn't miss out on this chance to just be together.

My husband's job is very mentally challenging.  It's high stress, and so for us this week was a lot of silence. He basically went into a coma like state. Which makes sense since the brain needs rest. But at times I felt like maybe I was boring? 

Oh how the enemy loves to lie. When in fact he's hugged me so many times today and said he had the best trip ever😉 He got what he needed...quiet. Intimacy. Slow. I challenge you to date your spouse. And try real hard not to create the perfect narrative in your mind. Step back. Be present and let God.

#palmsprings #dateyourspouse #love #rest #connection

Hi sweet friends. It's come to my attention that my book, "Seeing God in the Sweet Ordinary " is super low right now for Mother's day on various online shops. Amazon is $13.84 and Christian Books is $12.99🥳 It's a good time to stock up for gifts to hand out ALL year long. Teacher's gifts. Graduations. Momma. Birthdays. Christmas!! It's like a colorful love hug from the Lord. Pinky swear promise they'll love it:)) ❤️ Go read some of the reviews on Amazon. They blow me away. And if you haven't left me one...please do. It reallllly helps!!! Love you peeps!

I planted four huge troughs of multicolored pansies back in October. Best $200 ever!! They gave us beauty and color all winter long🙌 But now I'm ready to plant my favorite (zinnias) and the pansies are the happiest they've ever been🙈 I thought pansies died off in the spring?? Anyway, how does one dig up and disturb four huge troughs of perfectly beautiful flowers???? Thoughts...

Ya'll from the time I was a young momma I've dreamt of writing and illustrating a children's book. The other day the Lord downloaded every word and I'm taking that revelation and running with it. I truly have no idea what I'm doing, but I just know that I know it's going to be AMAZING!!!! He is faithful when we step out. He'll take my paint brush and swirl that paint. He'll give me the ideas and the vision. He'll see it to the end. We are ALL on assignment. I love seeing how He uses us for His kingdom work. If you've been dreaming/working on something I'd love to hear about it!!

Spring on the hill... My momma called me this morning and told me she was driving. I'm like where ya going. To your house she said🙈🙈🙊😳 Y'all I rarely know what day it is, but that one caught me off guard🤣 So momma Dixie is on her way and I can't wait to celebrate all the good things over the next few days. Pray she gets here safe. It's rainy, rush hour and she's recovering from cataract surgery🙏

I never had a sister. SO grateful these two are best friends and I get to be their momma. It's a pretty sweet gig🥰 Happy Mother's day friends! #mybesties #countingmyjoylist #sisters @audaciousdaughter @felicity.strahle
Beautiful inside and out...forever grateful I'm her girl🥰 #mommadixie #mothersday #countingmyjoylist

Y'all I made it to 50🙊🙌🥳 My friend Meg told me recently I was in my year of jubilee and I'm standing on that word. Here's to a year of celebrating all of God's goodness! 

I rarely do introductions, so hi!! I'm Becky, midwest girl, married to her Honey @levrage7 of 30 years, two grown creative daughters @audaciousdaughter @felicity.strahle.  We've spent the last 7 years fixing up our Tennessee hills property. We currently live 30-40 minutes south of Nashville.

For years I made leather cuffs. Then God shifted my sails and I started walking into my business name Farmgirl Paints. Painting is where I find so much freedom and joy. It's creating with my Creator (worship) and I'm so grateful I get to do it often. Last year I wrote my first book...Seeing God in the Sweet Ordinary. I'm currently working on a children's book, which is my absolute dream. Nature is where I get my inspiration and feel His presence the most. And traveling fills my heart to overflowing!!

Tell me about you. Who are you, where are you, and what do you love to do? I used to know people here. I miss those days...

We've had such a gloriously mild spring. Normally, we skip right into a blistering hot summer, but this year, we've had cool mornings, perfect temps, and stunning sunsets. 

A lot of people make lists of summer to-dos. I really just want to savor. I'd like to make it a point of catching every.single.sunset. I'd love to use our patio more and eat all of our meals outside. Maybe sip my coffee on my porch swing. Just readjust my habits to take in the view... To slow down, close my eyes and feel the sun, appreciate the breeze, and listen to the birds. If anything can bring you into His presence, it's a reset. A deliberate pause, posture alignment, and praise. What are your summer plans?

Ciao friends! Today was honestly a beautiful blur. I'm afraid if I don't photo dump at the end of each day, I'll never be able to make any sense of them all. 

We started with a historic tour of Bellagio with our sassy guide, Rita. She was fabulous. We went to the famous gardens here. I'm forgetting the name... It was stunning!! There is so much beauty that it's almost TOO much...if that can be a thing. After the gardens, we had lunch at NeNe. Then, just our fam decided to ferry over to Menaggio. Quick trip for a gelato and some fun finds, then back to our town for the most amazing dinner. 

My favorite part of the day was our evening stroll. The sun sets. The lamps light... It's quaint and calm. I could meander here forever. The women feel like old friends already. I absolutely can't wait to teach my class tomorrow.  I'm feeling so incredibly FULL in more ways than one😂🧁🍝❤️❤️❤️

The re-entry into the ordinary has been a tad harder than I thought. When you squeeze that much living into just a few days... coming home feels like you're on tilt. Our sleep is off. Our hearts crave the new and exciting.  Even my introverted nature longs for that constant companionship. Which is odd and wonderful all at once🙊

I never dreamt we'd have THAT much fun. But we did! I bathed that week in prayer for months and months, and boy did God hear me. I get weepy thinking about His love and tender care. 

One of my favorite chapters in the bible is Psalms 23. The verse "He prepares a table before me in the presence of my enemies..." Yep, that sums up this week! He fed our souls. He carved out a banquet table and met our unique needs. He's teaching us to trust. Despite storms... Despite the unexpected... He's gone before us and laid out the most beautiful spread, and all He asks of us is to keep our eyes on Him. To sit. To rest. To trust Him no matter what. 

I'm still unpacking my thoughts, but I do know this... God is good. And oh how He loves each and every one of us.

We've lived here for seven years, and for seven years, I've been drawn to this hiding "secret" place on our land. But for some reason, I never go. Today, the urge was too much to resist, and I loaded up the car and sat...surrounded by giant trees. Leaves falling all around me. The sunshine peeked through the tight spaces. Gusts would bend the branches in a dance just for me. My heart is full. Now I know why the deer gather here. They hide in His presence. Safe, surrounded.

I'm thinking about Maine this morning. Lifting up the brokenhearted.  Sometimes, it's hard to even know where to start when I pray... It goes something like this... Lord, help them. Heal them. Make my light brighter in this dark world. Use me as a beacon. You are all we have. We need You, desperately. 

I loved that about our time in Maine. The light houses reminded me of what my assignment is here in this temporary home. Light, light, light. It's easy to get overcome and lost in the darkness. But that light, His light pierces!!!🙌 Don't be tempted to hide.

I've been going down memory lane a lot in my mind recently.  We had to pivot our upcoming vacation plans, and instead of a trip to London and Scotland, we are heading back to Minnesota. You would think there would be sadness in that shift, but my heart is SO full of excitement I can hardly contain it. 

We raised our girls in MN, and it was a GOOD season. Friendships were deep. Memories were rooted. It was the best place for us for those seven years. And then God said it's time for something else... 

So 12 years ago, we drove away from what we knew and stepped into the new. Never looking back. And here we are now... The girls are grown, and our hearts are craving nostalgia.  A full circle, "holy spackle" trip. I'm so expectant. I know much has changed. But the things that matter are still the same. Despite the heavy and hard in the world, I'm chasing after closure, beauty...goodness. I'm taking notes on ordinary God moments that shape perspective and unearth buried soft spots. Stay tuned...

I found myself holding my breath through this one. Who knew letting go and trying to get loose would make you clam up and turn blue🙈😂😂 Breathe Becky!! I saw this print at a cute little boutique in Minnesota last week. As soon as I read it, I burst into tears. I think "imposter syndrome" is one of the biggest lies the enemy uses to keep us frozen. When, in fact, each one of us is equipped for using our gifts and talents for HIS glory!! 

What's holding you back? Is it the doubts tumbling in your mind, the algorithm...fear of rejection? I have zero doubt that we all struggle at times with those things, but He is ABLE to do abundantly more than we could ever dare to even ask. So let's ask. Let's move ahead no matter the mind games, the seemingly huge obstacles, the insecurities. He deserves it!!

There seems to be a lot of doomsday reporting lately. I avoid the news, but I catch snippets on social media etc... Elites are building bunkers, reporters are telling us how to stock pile supplies and brace for the big fall. Our government is spiraling, and in the midst, we as believers are reminded not to be deceived and not to be afraid. 

Read the Bible if you want to know how to live in these end times. Our hope is in Him and in Him alone. Reading through Matthew 21 this morning... as Jesus made His way into Jerusalem on a donkey's back. The people cried out Hosanna... which means save us. 

My heart lept at that revelation. Yes, Lord, we humbly lay at Your feet and cry out save us. Hosanna!!! You calmly rode into that city, knowing what lay ahead and did it for us. Hosanna! There's nothing to fear, You did it all!

#fgpbibleart #hosanna #faithbuilder #dailypainter #biblejournaling

Merry Christmas, friends! As we sang "O Holy Night" last night for the candlelit service, my heart latched onto the lyrics, "and the soul felt its worth." 

Our value isn't based on our gender, race, social or economic status its based on the fact that God loves us SO much He sent His son JESUS to live among us and to die for our sins. 

We can never be worthy on our own, but the lengths He went to to redeem and restore us make us worthy🙌  I am so grateful for my Savior, who came as a baby, born in a manger, who lived a blameless life, died and rose from the grave, so I could spend eternity with Him. He's here for us ALL if we set our eyes on Him and BELIEVE❤️ Merry Christmas!!!

The hangout...

I didn't always feel like I was the best momma when my girls were really little. Maybe it was too high of expectations of what a momma should be. But, I fought the blues a lot. I never wanted to play or even cook. 

That shifted in me as they got older. The depression lifted. I felt more present. I sought out things that we could do together that brought me joy. One of those things was walks at the Minnesota Arboretum. 

I'd pack up peanut butter and jelly sandwiches, pretzels, and juice boxes. We'd bundle up. I'd load them in the stroller, and we would make the three mile loop until we came to my favorite spot under the giant weeping willow tree. 

It was enormous. The branches spread out in a giant umbrella, cocooning us under its dancing branches and leaves. I'd pull out a blanket, say a little meal prayer, and we would picnic. 

It was what good mommas did. They made memories. They cherished time with their kiddos... That tree became a symbol to me of motherhood. My time enjoying my role as momma.

It was so weird going back recently. The tree from my memory was always what beckoned me, and when we saw it in person, it had changed. I wept... memories of how it HAD been flooding my mind. Was I remembering it wrong? No... The branches just no longer touched the ground. The cocoon was broken... Which seems fitting now that my girls are grown and beginning to spread their own wings. 

Just some musings on a cold winter morning. And if you are one of those mommas in the trenches, embrace each beautifully messy stage. I reflect back and see only good things. And I look forward with so much anticipation.  God is SO good!

Winter is usually my least favorite season, but I think I can safely say that's changed. 

I love the way the air feels crisp and dry. 

There's something about the bare branches stripped... minimal.

Night falls fast and beckons a break.

An unexpected blue sky brings pure joy.

Rhythms slow like a giant exhale. 

What are your favorite things about this season?

I love that this miracle was highlighted in Mark. The act of Jesus physically putting his fingers in the deaf man's ear. Also spitting and touching his tongue🥹 Looking to Heaven... He recognized the places that needed healing. He touched them. Ordered it to "Be Opened" and God!!🙌🙌 Do you have an area of your life that needs touched, spit upon... delivered? Jesus heals! The nooks and crannies of our hearts are His..if only we kneel before Him and ask.

What's your favorite way to splash paint? For me, learning how to paint on silk has been revolutionary. It started a year ago when the girls and I flew out to Colorado to see my niece @itsbrittanystuart with the goal of learning this new craft. Later that year, we jetted off to Bellagio, Italy, with @artandfaithcreative to teach a whole room full of women, our new favorite art form🙌

It has been a love affair of watching the ink bleed into the fabric...transforming that little square into something so special. I keep my scarf collection displayed in the art barn. They make me happy every time I walk by. 

THIS is what I'm teaching again in June🥳🥳🥳 It's so much fun, and anyone can do it. It's all about letting go, playing with color, and enjoying the process. Come with us this year. We have just three apartments left! See the link in my profile or reach out to @artandfaithcreative.

Our first (and possibly only snow) this year is perfection🥰  I've got some Glenn Miller tunes coming in strong in my headphones. I'm getting ready to do some much needed snow day cleaning. Our treat will be some games at the kitchen table later. I love a snow day😃 What are ya'll up to?

We played the game of "Life" last night. When you land on a Life square, you get a little tile that you get to turn over at the end. It equates money and the one with the most wins. 

Big events like kids, grandkids, weddings, etc. got a tile... But not travel. The game definitely needs an upgrade because traveling with my family and seeing the world has been absolutely priceless. At the end of my life, the back of the tiles might not have $$$ equations, but my memory/experience bank will be FULL:) 

These snippets were taken on Lake Como last Summer.  Where we had the honor to join Laura @artandfaithcreative to slow down, sit and savor time with our Creator, and create🙌 What a privilege. We head there again in June! I'll be teaching silk scarf painting😃 Won't you consider coming with us? It's eye-opening. Brave. A step of faith you won't regret.

I'm in Mark 14 this morning. Jesus tells Peter that before the rooster crows twice, he would deny him three times. Can you imagine Jesus telling you that? 

The truth is that Jesus knows us better than we know ourselves. Fear and self presevation are strong motivators, yet Peter's heart, despite the betrayal and shame, was remorseful...he wept bitterly, repented, and God still used him mightily. He later went on to win 3,000 souls for the kingdom🙌 

Do you have a past that makes you feel unworthy? That  bitter reminder can be a tool that the enemy uses to keep you from your assignment. Glean from Peter. Put it behind you and go about His business!😃
